<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
In 2.2.7 it is possible to apply modifiers (Fiery, Venom, ..., of Slay Foobar..) more than once. You need to be &gt;level 30 in alchemy, then create Fiery Foo, then make a Fiery Foo of Slay Bar. You now can apply another powerup, I don't remember if only "of Slay Baz" or even another Fiery. The weapon then is called "... of Slay Baz" (ie. you don't get a Fiery Venomenous Foo or a Foo of Slay Troll of Slay Orc), but the bonuses are rerolled each time and the flags get set (can make a poor man's Elemental Foo by applying all brands). <p>
This was not the case in 2.2.6 IIRC. 
</p>
<p>
Note: this doesn't work when having a (once-branded) "Fiery Foo" - can only apply "... of Slay Zomf" to those, as it should be. 
</p>
<p>
Simon: The second ego can be added infinitely in that version. If you add slaying first, you can add fiery as often as you want. But if you add fiery first, then you can add slaying as often as you want.  (as described by Da Alchemist, I didn't check) 
</p>
</div><div id="footer">


